Rare Candy}}<br>{{color2|000|Level|Level 14}}\n|no2=156\n|name2=Quilava\n|type1-2=Fire\n|evo2={{bag|Rare Candy}}<br>{{color2|000|Level|Level 36}}\n|no3=157\n|name3=Typhlosion\n|type1-3=Fire}}\n\n===Sprites===\n{{Spritebox/Header|type=fire}}\n{{Spritebox/NA|gen=II}}\n{{Spritebox/2|ndex=156}}\n{{Spritebox/3|ndex=156}}\n{{Spritebox/4|ndex=156}}\n{{Spritebox/5|ndex=156}}\n{{Spritebox/6|ndex=156}}\n{{Spritebox/7|ndex=156}}\n{{Spritebox/Footer|156|Quilava}}\n\n==Trivia==\n* Quilava shares its {{pkmn|category}} with {{p|Typhlosion}} and {{p|Entei}}. They are all known as the Volcano Pokémon.\n** Coincidentally, they all learn {{m|Eruption}}.\n\n===Origin===\nQuilava\'s body is similar to most animals in the {{wp|weasel}} family, particularly {{wp|stoat}}s due to its lack of a tail and the fur on its upper body being significantly darker than that on its underbelly. However, the pattern distribution and shape of Quilava\'s flames closely resembles the quills and crest of the {{wp|crested porcupine}}, especially in its earlier sprites. Its appearance is also quite close to a {{wp|paca}}, a South American rodent with a slender body, spotted skin, and tiny ears, as well as a {{wp|badger}}.\n\n====Name origin====\nQuilava is a combination of \'\'quill\'\' (a needle-like hair) and \'\'lava\'\' (extrusive molten rock).\n\nMagmarashi is a combination of \'\'magma\'\' and ヤマアラシ (山荒) \'\'yama-arashi\'\' ({{wp|porcupine}}).\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=fire|type2=fire\n|ja=マグマラシ \'\'Magmarashi\'\'|jameaning=From \'\'magma\'\' and {{wp|porcupine|{{tt|山荒 \'\'yama-arashi\'\'|porcupine}}}}\n|fr=Feurisson|frmeaning=From \'\'{{tt|feu|fire}}\'\' and \'\'{{tt|hérisson|hedgehog}}\'\'\n|es=Quilava|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Igelavar|demeaning=From \'\'{{tt|Igel|hedgehog}}\'\' and \'\'Lava\'\'\n|it=Quilava|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=마그케인 \'\'Mageukein\'\'|komeaning=From \'\'magma\'\' and {{tt|허리케인 \'\'heorikaein\'\'|huricane}}\n|zh_yue=火岩鼠 \'\'Fó\'ngàahmsyú\'\'|zh_yuemeaning=Means "Magma rodent"\n|zh_cmn=火岩鼠 \'\'Huŏyánshŭ\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=Means "Magma rodent"\n|hi=कुईलावा \'\'Quilava\'\'|himeaning=Transcription of English name\n|ru=Квилава \'\'Kvilava\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name\n}}\n<br clear="left">\n\n==Related articles==\n* [[Ash\'s Quilava]]\n* [[Dawn\'s Quilava]]\n* [[Exbo]]\n* [[Jimmy\'s Quilava]]\n* [[Starter Pokémon]]\n\n==External links==\n* {{wp|Cyndaquil, Quilava, and Typhlosion|Article on Wikipedia}}\n\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Fire}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Fire|species=Quilava|prevnum=155|prev=Cyndaquil|nextnum=157|next=Typhlosion|round=yes}}\n|}\n{{-}}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[Category:Shadow Pokémon in Pokémon Colosseum]]\n\n[[de:Igelavar]]\n[[es:Quilava]]\n[[fr:Feurisson]]\n[[it:Quilava]]\n[[ja:マグマラシ]]\n[[zh:火岩鼠]]'}